		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				I think that this was an enormous mistake.  I've played several cleric characters in EQ, and I know it for the dull and unforgiving job that it is.  If someone dies, it's your fault.  If you aren't paying attention every minute of every pull, someone WILL die.  At higher levels, the pattern of buff, heal, med, heal, stun, stun, heal, med, buff becomes mindnumbingly boring.  I hate playing a cleric... <br>  <br> Too bad they're so damned important.  Now in addition to a cleric's job being thankless in terms of gameplay, they've also made it nearly impossible.  At higher levels, the ONLY thing that separates clerics from druids and shamans is complete heal.  With the new agro nerf, using CH is a death sentence.  Clerics used to be the only ones with Superior Heal, but that changed after the Kunark expansion.  Now the only thing a cleric can do that someone can't do better is experience resses.  This is important, but it's not enough by itself. <br>  <br> I agree with the above thread.  If something doesn't change, the days of the cleric class, especially at level 52+, is numbered. <br>  <br> Cantini Harmless <br> Officer, LotU <br> Rage against Uber Guild Lighty!!!		

