		</tr>
		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				About medding during combat... <br>  <br> I understand that it is the most effective tactic -- especially on the blue servers.  However, I still find it absurd that as a battle where the very existence of every member of the group is hanging in the balance is raging, the clerics and wizards suddenly stop, assume the lotus position and enter a state of contemplative meditation.   <br>  <br> Compare your tactic in battles with monsters to those with groups of PvPers:  Do you sit down to meditate while being attacked by fellow players?  It would be suicidal to do so -- your defenses are lowered while sitting and hits tend to do maximum damage (you can test this theory in a friendly duel -- have someone hit you a few times while sitting and compare the damage with being hit while standing).  Other PvPers will take advantage of meditating casters.  Also consider that since we have coin-only loot the people who are the best targets are the powercampers -- the very people who use the medding in combat tactic the most (they will have piles of cash since they spend several hours in the same spot killing rich mosters).  Have you ever finished a battle completely drained of mana with many badly wounded members?  It is typical for campers -- they attack single monsters far above their level range for the better loot and exp (instead of killing many monsters that are even or yellow cons) -- burn off all their resources, then sit and med while waiting for the monster to spawn again so they can repeat the cycle (mindnumbingly boring to me -- which is why I solo).  Campers are quite vulnerable to PKing immediately after such a battle and it is to the discredit of our server that PKing scavengers are not more common. High mana consumption battles where medding during battle is required is a poor tactic on the PvP servers. <br>  <br> So why is medding during combat a valid tactic at all?  Poor AI.  If the situation were reversed and healer NPCs sat down to meditate when they had exhausted their mana (assuming they did not have their unlimited supply:), the PCs would immediately attack them.  Similarly, if your group were fighting 4 monsters -- one of which was doing complete heals on the other three whenever they got close to death -- you would kill the healer first.  All it would take is one complete heal to insure the death of the NPC healer.  Verant is moving toward a more intelligent AI, adding a bit of realism to the combat system and all the Clerics can do is whine about how their class has been &quot;nerfed&quot;.  Everquest is boring if you know you will win every combat and can predict exactly what the monster will do at every step.  Uncertainty is what brought me to the PvP servers and I am pleased to see it being added into even the blue servers.   <br> 		

			</td>
		</tr>
